│ %add.i.i.i = add i8 0, %conv678.i.i                                                                                                                                                      │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│ This is a first-order recurrence where the next value is computed by adding `0` to the current value. This is an identity operation: the value of `%conv678.i.i` starts at `1` and       │
│ remains `1` in every iteration. The correct final result of the function is `1`.                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The loop vectorizer incorrectly identifies this as a reduction. For an `add` operation, the identity element is `0`. The vectorizer seems to misuse this identity element during the     │
│ creation of the initial vector for the recurrence, resulting in `<i8 1, i8 0>` instead of the correct `<i8 1, i8 1>`. This leads to an incorrect final result of `2`.                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
